WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

03:38.425 --> 03:39.968
Check, charge or cash?

03:40.177 --> 03:41.219
Cash.

03:43.513 --> 03:45.015
Make it out to...

03:45.223 --> 03:47.059
Jack's Demolition. Tucson.

03:47.517 --> 03:49.061
$788.30.

05:39.680 --> 05:41.432
Taking me to breakfast?

05:41.807 --> 05:43.434
I can't. I'm meeting Bosko.

05:44.894 --> 05:46.145
Hey, Vincent.

05:46.437 --> 05:47.813
Where are my barrettes?

05:48.147 --> 05:50.107
I saw them on the kitchen table.

05:50.399 --> 05:51.692
I already checked.

05:52.193 --> 05:53.277
Coffee?

05:53.486 --> 05:54.537
No school today?

05:54.663 --> 05:57.832
My dad's taking me to the new building
and then to lunch.

05:58.041 --> 05:59.626
Try under the sofa cushions.

06:03.505 --> 06:05.548
He's already half an hour late.

06:06.174 --> 06:09.302
He's going to show,
or stand her up like last time?

06:09.678 --> 06:10.845
I'll make coffee.

06:11.137 --> 06:12.264
Out of time.

06:25.026 --> 06:27.570
Mom, my barrettes are not on the couch.

06:28.655 --> 06:30.323
Wear the blue ones.

06:30.740 --> 06:33.410
I don't want to wear the blue ones.
They don't match.

06:33.535 --> 06:36.329
- Did you check in your bathroom?
- I checked everywhere!

06:36.454 --> 06:37.831
What do you want me to do?

06:37.956 --> 06:39.082
Find them!

06:39.249 --> 06:42.127
- Mom, pay attention!
- All right, sweetie, all right!

06:42.335 --> 06:44.045
Daddy's going to be here.

06:44.170 --> 06:45.338
I won't be ready!

06:45.463 --> 06:47.048
- I can't be late.
- You won't.

06:47.173 --> 06:48.800
I will be late!

06:49.134 --> 06:51.970
Before Daddy comes,
we can find them if we look together.

06:52.095 --> 06:54.681
It's all right, baby. It's all right.

06:56.016 --> 06:58.893
We'll find them together, you and me.
We'll find them.

06:59.019 --> 07:02.856
Just relax. He won't come
before we find them. I promise you.

07:14.367 --> 07:15.952
Give me another refill.

07:27.797 --> 07:28.965
What's your name?

07:29.090 --> 07:30.300
Waingro.

07:39.151 --> 07:40.444
You're Michael?

07:53.499 --> 07:55.709
You guys always work together?

07:56.418 --> 07:57.836
All the time.

07:58.212 --> 07:59.546
Real tight crew?

07:59.755 --> 08:00.839
Real tight.

08:01.924 --> 08:05.386
If this works good,
I'd consider going again, you know.

08:05.803 --> 08:08.180
Yeah. Stop talking, okay, Slick?

08:18.857 --> 08:20.109
How's he doing?

08:20.276 --> 08:21.610
Hundred percent.

08:22.528 --> 08:23.994
Right on schedule.

08:24.619 --> 08:26.496
Made a right on Venice Boulevard.

08:28.373 --> 08:30.166
<i>We're a mile and a half from you.</i>

08:30.292 --> 08:31.376
Okay.

08:54.065 --> 08:57.068
Just crossed over the No. 1 lane,
300 yards from you.

08:57.819 --> 08:58.820
Get set.

08:58.987 --> 09:00.030
I am.

09:09.748 --> 09:10.790
Here we go.

10:11.235 --> 10:12.236
211!

10:12.569 --> 10:14.029
We're being held up!

10:20.035 --> 10:23.372
<i>- 211 alarm. Armored car.
- There's the call.</i>

10:23.497 --> 10:24.540
<i>Three minutes.</i>

10:26.166 --> 10:27.167
Clear!

11:31.324 --> 11:33.076
Eighty seconds left!

11:34.494 --> 11:36.621
Get back! Get back!

11:37.580 --> 11:38.623
Get back!

11:40.792 --> 11:44.837
Slick, see that shit coming out of
their ears? They can't fucking hear you!

11:45.004 --> 11:46.089
Cool it!

11:58.351 --> 11:59.477
I got it.

12:00.019 --> 12:01.145
Got it.

12:04.273 --> 12:06.192
You had to fuck with me.

12:06.609 --> 12:08.319
Want to fuck with me?

12:33.641 --> 12:35.439
What are you doing? What did he do?

12:35.564 --> 12:37.024
He was making a move.

12:46.616 --> 12:47.951
Dumb motherfucker.

13:19.024 --> 13:20.150
I heard them.

13:43.298 --> 13:44.841
$1.6 million...

13:45.801 --> 13:48.428
Forty cents on the dollar, $640,000 to you.

13:48.637 --> 13:50.555
Here's $150,000 front money.

13:51.473 --> 13:53.558
Get you the rest in two, three days.

13:54.768 --> 13:56.269
Who owned these?

14:00.273 --> 14:02.234
"Malibu Equity and Investments."

14:02.985 --> 14:04.361
Roger Van Zant.

14:04.486 --> 14:06.279
Owns banks in the Caymans...

14:06.405 --> 14:10.283
runs investment portfolios
for offshore drug money. Stuff like that.

14:10.575 --> 14:11.618
So?

14:11.827 --> 14:13.713
You ripped off his bearer bonds.

14:13.838 --> 14:15.006
He's insured.

14:16.090 --> 14:19.051
That's the point. He collects
100% from the insurance.

14:19.176 --> 14:21.804
He's a player. Maybe he buys
his bonds back from us...

14:21.929 --> 14:25.975
for 60% of their value.
Makes 40% on top of the 100%.

14:27.935 --> 14:31.063
Sell it back to him,
that's an extra $320,000 to you.

14:31.939 --> 14:32.982
Try it on.

14:33.983 --> 14:35.067
Kelso called.

14:35.192 --> 14:36.277
About what?

14:36.527 --> 14:39.322
A score he's putting out,
he wants you to look at.

14:39.780 --> 14:41.824
I don't need his score. I got my own.

14:42.033 --> 14:44.327
Says it's clean and low eight figures.

14:44.869 --> 14:46.078
9:00 a.m. Tomorrow.

14:46.203 --> 14:47.496
What happened?

14:48.956 --> 14:50.166
Don't ask.

15:25.576 --> 15:26.619
Find the ambulance?

15:26.744 --> 15:29.914
- Dumped it four blocks from here.
- 22nd Street.

15:30.873 --> 15:33.876
They torched it.
Burned the guns, clothes, everything.

15:36.420 --> 15:40.549
They were airborne. They taped the last
few seconds of the black-and-whites.

15:43.010 --> 15:45.221
Stolen from Fresno two weeks ago.

15:45.346 --> 15:48.349
Yellow pickup truck out of Whittier
a day before yesterday.

15:48.766 --> 15:50.059
You taking this one?

15:50.601 --> 15:52.478
Or does it stay in Division?

15:53.697 --> 15:57.158
Does this look like gangbangers
working the local 7-11 to you?

15:57.283 --> 15:59.160
Robbery-Homicide's taking it.

15:59.953 --> 16:01.287
We got three motorists.

16:01.413 --> 16:03.832
All they saw were men with masks.
They were distant.

16:03.957 --> 16:06.501
TV man over there, however,
he was closer.

16:08.128 --> 16:09.504
Did he ID anybody?

16:09.629 --> 16:12.090
He was hiding. He heard it mostly.

16:14.467 --> 16:16.052
What about them?

16:16.803 --> 16:20.056
According to the TV man,
this guy started mouthing off.

16:20.265 --> 16:21.307
Smart.

16:21.433 --> 16:23.518
Somebody called a guard "Slick."

16:25.103 --> 16:26.438
Now, I figure this guy...

16:26.563 --> 16:29.607
went for that hold-out piece, ankle holster.

16:30.442 --> 16:31.526
From here...

16:31.943 --> 16:33.069
bang, bang...

16:33.194 --> 16:34.654
bang, bang, bang.

16:35.071 --> 16:36.114
This side.

16:36.406 --> 16:40.994
This guy has got what appears to be
a double tap-entry wound to the sternum.

16:41.494 --> 16:44.497
Tattooing around the head wound,
scorched bone, close range.

16:44.622 --> 16:45.790
Probably executed.

16:47.959 --> 16:50.503
It was $1.6 million in bearer bonds.

16:50.670 --> 16:52.380
They ignored the loose cash.

16:52.505 --> 16:55.300
'Cause they had no time.
They were on a clock.

16:55.508 --> 16:58.219
Which means they knew
our response time to a 211...

16:58.345 --> 17:01.222
had our air, immobilized it, entered...

17:01.848 --> 17:03.975
escaped in under three minutes.

17:04.184 --> 17:06.935
It's a good spot here.
We got good escape routes.

17:07.103 --> 17:08.313
Two freeways...

17:08.521 --> 17:09.981
within a quarter of a mile.

17:10.106 --> 17:11.316
Traffic video camera?

17:11.775 --> 17:13.777
Probably disabled. Check it anyway.

17:13.902 --> 17:15.403
You recognize the M. O?

17:15.528 --> 17:16.695
M. O...

17:16.945 --> 17:18.323
is that they're good.

17:18.698 --> 17:22.911
Once it escalated into a murder-one
beef for all, after they killed two guards...

17:23.036 --> 17:24.371
they didn't hesitate.

17:24.496 --> 17:28.415
Popped guard No. 3 because...
what difference does it make?

17:28.875 --> 17:30.502
Why leave a living witness?

17:30.794 --> 17:33.680
Drop of a hat,
these guys will rock-and-roll.

17:36.725 --> 17:38.352
The shape charge.

17:38.769 --> 17:42.398
The shape charge indicates
that they are technically proficient.

17:42.523 --> 17:44.692
Proficient enough to go in on the prowl.

17:44.817 --> 17:48.153
Let's look for recent high-line burglaries
that have mystified us.

17:48.737 --> 17:51.907
Run "Slick" as an alias to the FBI.
You'll get the phone book.

17:52.032 --> 17:54.868
Do it anyway.
Who's moving the bearer bonds?

17:56.286 --> 17:59.832
Check the usual fences. You and I will
check Cuzomano and Torena.

17:59.957 --> 18:02.334
I want you to take Goldstein and Alfaro.

18:02.543 --> 18:03.919
Hang in with Forensics.

18:04.128 --> 18:06.755
From the bomb squad,
I want the explosive.

18:06.964 --> 18:09.758
If we're lucky, it's exotic.
We can trace the sale.

18:11.427 --> 18:14.054
Get your hand out of that man's pocket.

18:22.187 --> 18:23.689
Anyone want some pie?

18:33.365 --> 18:34.908
Gotta go to the john.

19:05.731 --> 19:09.568
I had to get it on. He was making a move.
I had to get it on.

19:23.174 --> 19:26.302
Split's in the car.
I took out of ours evenly...

19:27.637 --> 19:29.681
to make up for his full end...

19:30.431 --> 19:34.477
'cause I want to pay off and get rid
of this motherfucker right now.

20:13.391 --> 20:14.434
Hold it!

21:54.501 --> 21:55.711
Where's the rest?

21:55.836 --> 21:58.630
We're late. You look too good to go out.

21:59.005 --> 22:00.882
I'll just jump you right here.

22:04.428 --> 22:07.055
- Where is it?
- Squared the bookies, baby.

22:07.305 --> 22:10.392
There's more in a couple of days,
so don't sweat it. We're late.

22:10.517 --> 22:11.560
Come on.

22:11.685 --> 22:13.353
You gotta be kidding me.

22:15.063 --> 22:16.189
Honey...

22:16.314 --> 22:21.028
it ain't worth the risks you take
for $8,000. Like in "Risk versus reward."

22:21.278 --> 22:22.320
Let's go.

22:22.446 --> 22:23.780
Get your coat.

22:25.782 --> 22:28.869
There's no point talking.
You're just a child growing older.

22:29.036 --> 22:30.370
What does that mean?

22:30.704 --> 22:34.717
We're not making forward progress
like real grown-up adults living our lives...

22:34.842 --> 22:37.011
because I married a gambling junkie.

22:37.553 --> 22:39.346
Get in the fucking car.

22:41.140 --> 22:42.808
What am I doing in here?

22:43.309 --> 22:44.351
You're not!

22:44.477 --> 22:47.146
Leave the bank book and the car keys...

22:47.271 --> 22:48.856
in the kitchen on your way out!

22:48.981 --> 22:52.818
- Are we going?
- Keep that crap. Dominick comes with me.

22:54.987 --> 22:56.697
Don't even think about...

23:21.389 --> 23:24.100
Tell me Albert Torena called back.

23:25.184 --> 23:26.894
Albert Torena call Vincent?

23:28.104 --> 23:29.313
No.

23:29.438 --> 23:30.856
Report came in.

23:31.524 --> 23:34.151
<i>The explosive was Dy-Ex,
used in demolition.</i>

23:34.402 --> 23:36.362
<i>You can pick it up in Nevada...</i>

23:36.529 --> 23:38.072
Arizona, New Mexico.

23:38.406 --> 23:40.157
Too common to trace a sale.

23:40.533 --> 23:42.118
That's wonderful.

24:02.346 --> 24:03.347
You all right?

24:03.973 --> 24:06.100
What happened? Where have you been?

24:06.726 --> 24:07.768
Work.

24:09.061 --> 24:10.813
Lauren's dad show up?

24:12.565 --> 24:13.608
Didn't call...

24:13.742 --> 24:16.536
didn't show. We waited for you till 10:30.

24:17.954 --> 24:21.791
Now, does this guy have any idea
what's going on with this kid?

24:24.335 --> 24:25.545
I don't know.

24:26.588 --> 24:28.006
Fucking jerk.

24:29.758 --> 24:30.967
Is she okay?

24:32.093 --> 24:34.137
She's been in her room all day.

24:34.345 --> 24:36.973
So, no, she's not okay. Neither am I.

24:37.599 --> 24:39.059
I made dinner...

24:39.476 --> 24:41.436
for us, four hours ago.

24:43.188 --> 24:46.191
Every time I try to maintain
a consistent mood between us...

24:46.316 --> 24:47.650
you withdraw.

24:48.777 --> 24:52.238
I got three dead bodies on a sidewalk...

24:52.364 --> 24:54.741
off Venice Boulevard, Justine.

24:54.991 --> 24:56.326
I'm sorry...

24:56.785 --> 24:58.495
if the goddamn...

24:59.204 --> 25:00.497
chicken...

25:01.289 --> 25:02.916
got overcooked.

25:59.654 --> 26:00.780
Coffee, sir?

26:00.989 --> 26:01.990
Please.

26:07.662 --> 26:09.330
Will you pass the cream?

26:11.958 --> 26:13.043
Thanks.

26:13.168 --> 26:14.377
What'd you get?

26:15.628 --> 26:16.629
What?

26:17.630 --> 26:19.090
What are you reading?

26:24.846 --> 26:26.264
Book about metals.

26:30.060 --> 26:31.936
<i>Stress Fractures in Titanium.</i>

26:34.314 --> 26:35.982
What kind of work do you do?

26:39.152 --> 26:42.405
Lady, why are you so interested
in what I read or what I do?

26:46.826 --> 26:48.578
I've seen you in the store.

26:48.703 --> 26:49.954
What store?

26:50.371 --> 26:52.373
Hennessey and Ingalls. I work there.

26:54.334 --> 26:56.795
If you don't want to talk to me, it's okay.

26:57.003 --> 26:58.671
I'm sorry I bothered you.

27:09.057 --> 27:12.185
I didn't mean to be rude.
I didn't recognize you.

27:13.061 --> 27:15.355
I work in metals. I'm a salesman.

27:15.688 --> 27:17.023
My name's Neil.

27:22.362 --> 27:23.530
I'm Eady.

27:26.408 --> 27:27.992
You like working there?

27:29.744 --> 27:30.829
Sure.

27:31.538 --> 27:35.217
I get a discount and there's
a whole section of books in my area.

27:35.426 --> 27:36.510
What area?

27:37.052 --> 27:38.512
Graphic design.

27:39.430 --> 27:42.474
I do letterheads and logotypes
at night and...

27:43.225 --> 27:46.061
the store's a day job
until I get enough going.

27:46.270 --> 27:47.855
Who do you do that for?

27:50.941 --> 27:52.359
A restaurant.

27:52.901 --> 27:54.862
I did their menus, and...

27:57.573 --> 27:59.700
a small record label.

28:00.909 --> 28:01.910
CDs.

28:02.453 --> 28:04.204
I've done two so far.

28:06.582 --> 28:08.250
You go to school for that?

28:08.792 --> 28:09.835
Yeah.

28:10.919 --> 28:12.254
I went to Parsons.

28:12.421 --> 28:13.589
Where's that?

28:13.881 --> 28:15.048
New York City.

28:15.883 --> 28:17.468
How long you been here?

28:18.594 --> 28:19.928
About a year.

28:20.929 --> 28:22.056
Like it?

28:23.932 --> 28:26.727
Not really. I'm mostly here for the work.

28:34.443 --> 28:36.111
Live in this neighborhood?

28:36.236 --> 28:38.989
No, I live kind of above Sunset Plaza.

28:41.950 --> 28:43.368
It's a little house I rent.

28:43.494 --> 28:47.081
And it's kind of rundown,
but a beautiful, beautiful view.

28:48.665 --> 28:49.875
What about you?

28:50.000 --> 28:51.251
I live up here.

28:51.460 --> 28:52.836
That's very funny.

28:57.174 --> 28:59.468
Where's your family from originally?

29:02.012 --> 29:03.764
They're Scotch-Irish.

29:04.640 --> 29:06.767
They emigrated to Appalachia...

29:06.892 --> 29:08.936
in the late 1700s.

29:11.647 --> 29:13.107
Where are you from?

29:13.866 --> 29:15.159
The Bay area.

29:16.661 --> 29:17.995
Your folks there?

29:21.082 --> 29:23.543
My mother died a long time ago,
and my father...

29:23.668 --> 29:25.211
I don't know where he is.

29:25.336 --> 29:26.963
Got a brother somewhere.

29:32.844 --> 29:34.804
You have a tight family. I can tell.

29:36.180 --> 29:37.181
Right?

29:37.390 --> 29:38.683
You're right.

29:48.526 --> 29:50.153
City of lights.

29:53.573 --> 29:55.116
In Fiji, they have...

29:55.241 --> 29:58.911
iridescent algae that come out
once a year in the water.

30:00.204 --> 30:02.331
That's what it looks like out there.

30:03.583 --> 30:04.876
You been there?

30:06.252 --> 30:08.171
No, I'm going there someday.

30:17.263 --> 30:18.598
You travel a lot?

30:21.559 --> 30:22.602
Yeah.

30:22.977 --> 30:24.729
Traveling make you lonely?

30:29.942 --> 30:31.819
I'm alone. I am not...

30:32.278 --> 30:33.571
lonely.

30:33.946 --> 30:34.989
You?

30:36.616 --> 30:37.992
Real lonely.

32:43.052 --> 32:44.220
Albert!

32:47.014 --> 32:48.057
Shit!

32:49.975 --> 32:52.645
What you doing here? You crazy?
This ain't Disneyland.

32:52.770 --> 32:54.897
You were supposed to get back to me.

32:55.022 --> 32:56.816
Where the fuck you been?

32:57.858 --> 32:59.401
I couldn't break free.

32:59.527 --> 33:01.529
Let's violate his ass right now.

33:01.737 --> 33:03.239
I do for you...

33:03.531 --> 33:05.866
you don't do for me, is that it?

33:06.575 --> 33:10.996
Vincent, man. I swear, I was out all night.
I'm hitting like a Flamingo matador.

33:11.205 --> 33:13.499
That's got nothing to do with me.

33:13.749 --> 33:18.337
I'm cutting it smooth. I'm generating
leads and shit for you. I'm a dancer.

33:18.546 --> 33:19.839
You bullshit.

33:20.047 --> 33:22.466
I paged your ass all day.
I hate fucking paging.

33:22.591 --> 33:25.136
You're a speed freak,
jacking methamphetamine again.

33:25.261 --> 33:28.139
Where's your empathy?
It's a substance abuse problem.

33:28.264 --> 33:31.892
Empathy was yesterday. Today you're
wasting my motherfucking time.

33:32.017 --> 33:33.561
You fall in love?

33:35.146 --> 33:36.730
Did you fall in love...

33:36.939 --> 33:38.649
and went off somewhere?

33:38.774 --> 33:40.985
Tell me that, I'll settle for it.

33:43.070 --> 33:44.530
Give me all you got!

33:44.905 --> 33:46.574
Give me all you got!

33:46.991 --> 33:50.661
I swear, my brother Richard's going
to talk to you.

33:50.786 --> 33:52.371
I heard Richard?

33:53.122 --> 33:54.790
He's going to talk to you.

33:56.584 --> 33:58.169
He's gonna meet you tonight.

33:58.294 --> 33:59.795
He's not here, is he?

33:59.920 --> 34:01.338
No, he'll meet you tonight.

34:01.464 --> 34:02.965
What happened to now?

34:03.299 --> 34:07.011
I implored him because I knew
you was coming this a.m.

34:07.136 --> 34:08.179
Bullshit.

34:08.304 --> 34:10.431
I swear. He said no...

34:10.764 --> 34:12.683
'cause he in Phoenix.

34:12.850 --> 34:15.110
<i>By the time I get to Phoenix</i>

34:15.820 --> 34:17.489
<i>He'll be rising</i>

34:19.157 --> 34:20.949
<i>He'll probably leave a note</i>

34:21.326 --> 34:22.869
<i>Right on the door</i>

34:22.994 --> 34:25.121
Tonight's the best I can do for you.

34:26.831 --> 34:30.460
He'll meet you at BJ's on Alvarado.

34:31.668 --> 34:32.712
At 2:00 a.m.

34:32.837 --> 34:33.880
Be there.

34:34.005 --> 34:35.590
You be there, too.

34:36.174 --> 34:38.551
I can't be there, man. I got things to do.

34:38.676 --> 34:41.513
I got things to do, I got places to be.

34:42.847 --> 34:43.931
Be there.

34:50.063 --> 34:52.232
Don't waste my motherfucking time!

34:56.485 --> 34:57.612
What is it?

34:59.364 --> 35:00.615
It's a bank.

35:00.949 --> 35:04.536
It depos cash on Thursday for distribution
to all the other branches...

35:04.661 --> 35:06.704
to cover Friday payroll checks.

35:06.830 --> 35:09.999
So on Thursdays,
the command branch has got a full whack.

35:10.166 --> 35:11.626
On the prowl or strong?

35:11.751 --> 35:12.836
Strong. Through the door.

35:12.961 --> 35:14.045
How many guys?

35:14.170 --> 35:17.924
About four, or three, plus a driver.
You walk in, knock 'em over, walk out.

35:18.049 --> 35:21.511
You want $100,000 in advance
against a ten-percent cut for that?

35:22.220 --> 35:23.972
Sounds like a cowboy score.

35:24.180 --> 35:27.725
They hit the hold-up alarms,
I gotta get out before the cops show.

35:28.560 --> 35:30.854
They hit three hold-up alarm systems.

35:31.187 --> 35:32.981
Two Telco and a cellular.

35:35.024 --> 35:37.694
But the signals aren't
going anywhere because...

35:38.069 --> 35:39.654
the night before...

35:39.904 --> 35:41.197
you cut in...

35:41.406 --> 35:43.992
and trick out the alarm system computer...

35:44.200 --> 35:45.452
to turn itself...

35:45.577 --> 35:47.662
and the video recorders off...

35:48.037 --> 35:49.998
20 minutes before you enter.

35:50.540 --> 35:52.500
Architectural, electrical plans?

35:52.625 --> 35:53.760
I got that.

35:53.886 --> 35:56.805
I got the boards already built.
They go right into the CPU.

35:58.223 --> 35:59.683
What's the estimate?

36:03.103 --> 36:05.230
$12.1, $12.2 million.

36:08.317 --> 36:09.359
You're on.

36:10.527 --> 36:11.737
Congratulations.

36:12.404 --> 36:16.074
Let me give you a little idea
of where my estimates come from.

36:16.283 --> 36:18.577
Nobody knew the merch was yours.

36:18.952 --> 36:21.747
My way, you get 100%
from the insurance company...

36:21.872 --> 36:23.791
take the bonds back from us...

36:23.916 --> 36:27.419
<i>at 60 cents on the dollar
and make yourself another 40%.</i>

36:29.463 --> 36:32.090
The operation doesn't skip a beat.
We all make out.

36:33.300 --> 36:34.718
Sure, you got a deal.

36:35.511 --> 36:38.847
Good, because there's no percentage
if everyone gets upset.

36:39.473 --> 36:42.184
You have your man call me
and we'll set the meet.

36:42.559 --> 36:43.644
Yeah, okay.

36:44.478 --> 36:45.938
Nice talking to you.

36:46.939 --> 36:48.649
You gonna deal with these guys?

36:48.774 --> 36:51.610
Word's on the street
it's okay to steal my stuff.

36:51.735 --> 36:54.154
I'm going to kill these sons of bitches.

36:54.279 --> 36:57.491
Have Harry bring me the spreadsheets
for Canary Island's Offshore.

37:02.704 --> 37:05.374
That's not really an estimate.
Those are exact figures.

37:05.499 --> 37:08.710
I have a printout of the bank's cash flow
for the past two months.

37:08.836 --> 37:10.462
How'd you get this information?

37:10.712 --> 37:11.964
Just comes to you.

37:12.089 --> 37:14.508
This stuff just flies through the air.

37:14.633 --> 37:18.220
It's just beamed out all over the place.
You just have to grab it.

37:18.345 --> 37:19.930
I know how to grab it.

37:25.853 --> 37:27.479
Okay, here we go.

37:28.021 --> 37:29.481
$13.9 million.

37:33.152 --> 37:34.579
- I bought it.
- Good.

37:35.037 --> 37:36.497
What did I tell you?

37:40.334 --> 37:41.377
Here.

37:42.545 --> 37:45.423
We're on. Call Van Zant,
collect the money.

37:46.674 --> 37:47.800
How is he?

37:48.217 --> 37:49.677
He's a businessman.

38:27.673 --> 38:29.133
Chris is at my place.

38:32.553 --> 38:33.721
What's wrong?

38:34.055 --> 38:35.890
Husband-and-wife stuff.

38:36.557 --> 38:38.226
I'll let him sleep it off.

38:52.615 --> 38:54.075
What happened to you?

38:58.287 --> 39:00.331
When will you get some furniture?

39:00.456 --> 39:02.125
When I get around to it.

39:04.794 --> 39:06.712
Charlene's gonna leave me.

39:09.132 --> 39:10.174
Why?

39:13.302 --> 39:15.397
Not enough steaks in the freezer.

39:16.439 --> 39:18.483
With everything we've been doing?

39:19.609 --> 39:22.237
Vegas and the Super Bowl cleaned me out.

39:23.155 --> 39:25.115
When you gonna get an old lady?

39:25.282 --> 39:26.908
When I get around to it.

39:29.327 --> 39:31.413
You got something else on the side?

39:32.998 --> 39:34.291
Nothing regular.

39:35.292 --> 39:37.419
She got something else on the side?

39:37.544 --> 39:38.837
- No.
- You sure?

39:40.005 --> 39:41.465
Yeah, I'm sure.

39:43.675 --> 39:45.635
I don't know what you're doing.

39:47.179 --> 39:51.224
As Jimmy said, "You want to be
making moves on the street?

39:51.349 --> 39:54.811
"Have no attachments.
Allow nothing to be in your life...

39:55.020 --> 39:59.566
"that you can't walk out on in 30 seconds
if you spot the heat around the corner."

39:59.983 --> 40:01.151
Remember that?

40:08.200 --> 40:10.952
For me, the sun rises
and sets with her, man.

40:25.050 --> 40:27.385
We take the delivery of cash
from Van Zant...

40:27.511 --> 40:30.472
then I drop a deposit on Kelso
for this bank.

40:30.722 --> 40:32.057
Bank? What bank?

40:32.557 --> 40:35.310
What about the platinum thing?
It's ready to fall.

40:35.435 --> 40:37.312
That goes, too. Then the bank.

40:41.399 --> 40:42.859
Want some breakfast?

40:50.367 --> 40:51.701
Are you okay?

40:52.202 --> 40:53.537
Yeah, sugar.

41:01.053 --> 41:02.221
For real.

41:02.346 --> 41:03.472
I'll do good.

41:03.722 --> 41:05.141
I'll see you later.

41:21.073 --> 41:22.408
You Solenko?

41:22.825 --> 41:23.909
I'm Don Breedan.

41:24.118 --> 41:28.289
Grierson, my parole officer, told me
to come here, see if you had a job for me.

41:28.414 --> 41:30.624
You're familiar with this kind of operation?

41:30.749 --> 41:32.418
I'm a great grill man.

41:32.626 --> 41:33.961
Good. Good for you.

41:34.086 --> 41:38.132
You'll mop the toilets, hit the dishwasher,
bus tables and empty the garbage.

41:38.257 --> 41:41.677
Give me a hard time, I'll report you loaded,
drunk or stealing.

41:41.802 --> 41:43.639
I'll violate you back fast.

41:43.894 --> 41:46.605
Twenty-five percent of your take-home
kicks back to me.

41:46.730 --> 41:50.942
Rules of the game. Call Grierson,
check it out. Change in the back.

41:57.324 --> 41:59.117
What are you waiting for?

42:18.887 --> 42:20.597
<i>Malibu Equity and Investments.</i>

42:20.722 --> 42:22.224
Roger Van Zant.

42:22.349 --> 42:23.475
<i>Please hold.</i>

42:27.229 --> 42:29.105
<i>This is Roger Van Zant.</i>

42:29.689 --> 42:31.483
I'm supposed to collect something.

42:31.900 --> 42:34.495
Someone will call you back
from another line.

42:36.038 --> 42:38.874
818-133-6089.

43:04.150 --> 43:08.404
<i>I got a package for you. There's a drive-in
on Centinela. 2:30 tomorrow.</i>

43:08.654 --> 43:10.614
Just send one man, alone.

43:36.474 --> 43:38.392
- Who was that guy?
- Nobody.

43:39.685 --> 43:41.353
- Who was that guy?
- Nobody.

43:41.770 --> 43:43.689
I gotta know who he is! Who is he?

43:43.856 --> 43:44.982
He's nobody, Neil.

43:45.107 --> 43:48.569
He's a legit liquor wholesaler
from Las Vegas. Alan Marciano.

43:48.986 --> 43:50.488
Chris will make up.

43:50.613 --> 43:53.240
- It's too late! I'm sick of it!
- Shut up!

43:54.950 --> 43:58.287
Here's the deal.
You'll give Chris one last shot.

43:58.412 --> 44:02.374
After that, he fucks up,
then I will finance setting you up myself...

44:02.625 --> 44:04.752
on my own, anywhere you want.

44:04.919 --> 44:06.587
Dominick will go with you.

44:06.795 --> 44:09.089
And my word counts. But right now...

44:09.465 --> 44:11.759
you will give him the chance.

44:15.980 --> 44:17.607
Clean up. Go home.

44:18.983 --> 44:20.610
Clean up. Go home!

45:06.698 --> 45:07.991
Give me all your money.

45:08.116 --> 45:10.118
You'll get smoked with that shit.

45:10.243 --> 45:11.411
Won't be you.

45:14.622 --> 45:16.666
He's coming in alone. Send him through.

45:47.447 --> 45:49.073
Vincent, hey, man.

45:52.327 --> 45:54.588
This is my brother, Richard. Vincent.

45:54.755 --> 45:56.215
It's all right.

45:57.466 --> 45:59.343
What have you got for me?

45:59.635 --> 46:04.097
Before we even get into that, there's
this crew ripping rides all along the beach.

46:06.141 --> 46:08.310
Now, in the back of a trim shop...

46:08.477 --> 46:11.688
if somebody wants to pay
a little visit this weekend...

46:11.813 --> 46:14.942
they might find two Turbos
and a 911 Slope.

46:15.901 --> 46:18.570
You're looking to rid yourself
of your competition?

46:19.780 --> 46:21.448
I'm a good citizen.

46:21.573 --> 46:23.116
I'm Donald Duck.

46:23.450 --> 46:25.285
You got something to tell me?

46:26.954 --> 46:28.705
Check this out, cuz.

46:29.623 --> 46:32.918
How do I know if I tell you
what you need to know...

46:33.293 --> 46:36.630
that you're gonna do
what the fuck I need to get done.

46:37.339 --> 46:39.091
Hanna is straight up.

46:39.925 --> 46:42.177
I ain't your cuz, you rat motherfucker.

46:42.302 --> 46:44.596
And you know because I say so...

46:45.222 --> 46:48.016
after I hear what the fuck
you got to tell me!

46:48.141 --> 46:49.226
Fuck you.

46:49.351 --> 46:50.602
You understand?

46:50.894 --> 46:52.855
I can get killed for telling you this.

46:52.980 --> 46:55.190
You can get killed walking your doggie!

46:55.315 --> 46:56.608
All right, man...

46:57.192 --> 46:59.570
there was a cat I was locked up with.

46:59.736 --> 47:04.074
Did a couple of two, three years.
He got out. I ran into him.

47:06.994 --> 47:08.120
And so?

47:08.579 --> 47:11.206
He's a big fiend for action.

47:11.331 --> 47:14.960
Now, if he'd have said nothing,
I'd have thought nothing, but...

47:15.085 --> 47:18.463
he goes on and on,
telling me how he ain't done nothing...

47:18.589 --> 47:21.341
and nothing's been going on,
and all this bullshit.

47:21.466 --> 47:23.427
Right then and there I know...

47:24.011 --> 47:26.638
this cat's got something going down.

47:34.238 --> 47:35.948
Pretty fucking great.

47:37.700 --> 47:39.911
Albert, what's wrong with you?

47:40.661 --> 47:44.123
You drag me here,
waste my time like this.

47:44.248 --> 47:47.251
You saw a guy on the street
who's an ex-con?

47:47.376 --> 47:48.419
That's right.

47:48.544 --> 47:50.004
Well, I am...

47:50.213 --> 47:51.881
over-fucking-whelmed.

47:52.298 --> 47:54.800
What do you want for that,
a junior G-man badge?

47:55.218 --> 47:57.553
You gonna make the call
on them Porsches?

47:58.471 --> 47:59.805
Is he kidding me?

48:01.224 --> 48:02.266
I'm telling you:

48:02.391 --> 48:03.935
This Slick is no joke.

48:04.393 --> 48:05.895
He's double time.

48:06.020 --> 48:07.230
Say what?

48:07.980 --> 48:09.899
"Slick." What does that mean?

48:10.066 --> 48:12.485
That's what he calls people: "Slick."

48:14.111 --> 48:15.738
Tell me about him.

48:17.990 --> 48:19.826
About 6 feet tall...

48:20.117 --> 48:22.078
lots of jailhouse tats.

48:22.203 --> 48:24.330
Got a big-ass peacock right here.

48:26.874 --> 48:28.334
What's his name?

48:29.252 --> 48:30.545
Cheritto.

48:31.295 --> 48:33.422
Michael Cheritto.

48:37.260 --> 48:39.846
<i>Thirty-three busts since 1976.</i>

48:39.971 --> 48:42.515
<i>Eleven for armed robbery,
three convictions.</i>

48:42.682 --> 48:45.309
<i>Two out of a three-to-five year beef
in Attica.</i>

48:45.434 --> 48:46.602
Three years in Marion.

48:46.727 --> 48:49.981
Five years in Folsom off a knock-back
to involuntary manslaughter.

48:50.106 --> 48:51.357
<i>Jacket's two inches thick.</i>

48:51.482 --> 48:53.401
Who do I have there now?

48:53.526 --> 48:56.237
<i>- Drucker and me. And Schwartz.
- Tell SIS...</i>

48:56.362 --> 49:00.241
I want full surveillance. That's 24 hours.
Round the clock, day and night.

49:00.366 --> 49:02.535
We never close. Open every day.

49:02.785 --> 49:04.579
<i>Bug the car, the house, the work.</i>

49:04.704 --> 49:06.914
<i>When he moves or sits,
like in a restaurant...</i>

49:07.039 --> 49:09.500
<i>I want pictures of who he moves
and sits with.</i>

49:09.625 --> 49:12.920
Then run makes on them.
They got jackets, trail them.

49:13.421 --> 49:15.891
I want it up and running
by tomorrow night.

50:11.404 --> 50:13.573
Put your hands where I can see them.

50:13.823 --> 50:15.992
Put your hands where I can see them.

50:16.868 --> 50:18.245
I tell you what to do.

50:18.370 --> 50:20.080
I tell you how to do it.

50:20.914 --> 50:24.334
Now, with your right hand only,
your right hand only...

50:26.002 --> 50:28.421
take the package and throw it in here.

50:46.314 --> 50:47.440
Behind you.

50:47.566 --> 50:48.775
<i>On the right.</i>

52:08.113 --> 52:09.532
Roger Van Zant.

52:10.157 --> 52:11.283
Who's this?

52:11.784 --> 52:13.244
You know who this is.

52:14.161 --> 52:15.454
Yes, I do.

52:15.996 --> 52:17.957
<i>I sent a guy to deliver the package.</i>

52:18.082 --> 52:20.251
He didn't call. Is everything okay?

52:21.085 --> 52:23.295
<i>I tell you what, forget the money.</i>

52:23.879 --> 52:24.922
What?

52:25.673 --> 52:27.299
Forget the money.

52:29.844 --> 52:33.898
It's a lot of money. What are you doing?
What do you mean, "Forget the money"?

52:34.023 --> 52:36.901
What am I doing?
I'm talking to an empty telephone.

52:37.819 --> 52:39.237
I don't understand.

52:39.821 --> 52:42.991
'Cause there is a dead man
on the other end of this line.

53:04.220 --> 53:05.471
Do you like it?

53:05.597 --> 53:06.973
Look at my ring.

53:12.395 --> 53:13.605
Did you know?

53:15.148 --> 53:16.649
You are insane.

53:21.905 --> 53:23.031
Do you like it?

53:23.156 --> 53:25.116
- It's beautiful.
- It's good.

53:25.283 --> 53:27.202
Don't ask him where he got it.

53:36.002 --> 53:38.338
What do you want to be
when you grow up?

53:38.713 --> 53:39.881
I don't know.

53:42.967 --> 53:44.344
Just like me.

53:44.469 --> 53:45.970
I don't know either.

54:00.568 --> 54:01.611
Hello?

54:02.320 --> 54:03.530
It's me.

54:05.281 --> 54:07.325
I was wondering if you'd call.

54:08.993 --> 54:10.286
I've been busy.

54:10.620 --> 54:11.913
Can I see you?

54:12.372 --> 54:14.258
I was afraid that was just...

54:15.217 --> 54:16.760
the one night.

54:17.928 --> 54:19.763
Not for me, it wasn't.

54:22.307 --> 54:23.767
Yeah, me neither.

54:25.978 --> 54:27.437
Can I fall by?

54:28.814 --> 54:29.898
Yeah.

54:30.148 --> 54:32.025
I'll see you in a little bit.

54:47.165 --> 54:48.834
Goddamn convention.

54:50.127 --> 54:52.296
- Which one's Slick?
- The wide one.

54:52.629 --> 54:54.298
We got two transmitters.

54:54.590 --> 54:57.342
One's in the wheel well,
backup's in the firewall.

54:57.467 --> 54:58.510
Here we are.

54:58.635 --> 55:00.596
Did you say goodnight to Neil?

55:01.346 --> 55:03.307
The blond is Chris Shiherlis.

55:03.432 --> 55:06.935
SIS has got a revolving tail
and hung a wire on the house phone.

55:09.479 --> 55:12.608
Cheritto's cruised the precious-metals
depository three times.

55:12.733 --> 55:15.027
Platinum, silver, and some bullion.

55:16.028 --> 55:18.614
Sammy and I think that will be
their next score.

55:18.739 --> 55:20.073
Who's the loner?

55:23.285 --> 55:24.745
First time we've seen him.

55:24.870 --> 55:26.413
We're not on him yet.

55:28.582 --> 55:29.875
Get on it.

55:47.726 --> 55:52.397
When these guys walk out the door of
whatever score they're gonna take next...

55:54.367 --> 55:57.495
they're gonna have the surprise
of a lifetime.

56:13.261 --> 56:14.887
Baby, time to go.

56:16.514 --> 56:18.891
Showed you a good time, didn't I?

56:22.436 --> 56:23.563
You fly.

56:23.771 --> 56:25.022
You're cool.

56:32.655 --> 56:36.367
You're lying to me.
I can always tell when people lie to me.

56:37.285 --> 56:38.578
I ain't lying.

56:39.328 --> 56:40.788
You're a hot dog.

56:41.455 --> 56:43.249
A regular rodeo rider.

56:43.958 --> 56:46.961
And this was the monster fuck
of my young life.

56:51.507 --> 56:54.260
Now, I got to get my ass
street-side, sugar.

56:54.385 --> 56:56.596
You don't have a truth-telling style.

56:56.804 --> 56:58.598
What are you talking about?

56:58.806 --> 57:00.892
You don't know what this is.

57:07.440 --> 57:09.901
The Grim Reaper's visiting with you.

57:28.669 --> 57:30.004
Where have you been?

57:31.631 --> 57:33.299
SHU at Pelican Bay.

57:33.677 --> 57:35.393
Folsom, B-wing.

57:36.353 --> 57:37.896
I am a cowboy...

57:38.730 --> 57:40.607
looking for anything heavy.

57:40.732 --> 57:42.817
Billy said to come see you.

57:43.568 --> 57:45.403
That is why I am here.

57:54.412 --> 57:57.082
Why don't you call this guy?

57:58.166 --> 58:00.377
This guy's always putting guys on.

58:04.506 --> 58:05.549
Thank you.

58:20.063 --> 58:21.898
You're perfect for each other.

58:27.743 --> 58:29.620
I knew a guy in grade school.

58:29.996 --> 58:32.290
His name was Raoul... whatever.

58:32.415 --> 58:35.960
You could take his fingers
and fold them over each other.

58:36.252 --> 58:38.296
He'd turn his eyelids inside out...

58:38.421 --> 58:41.382
I can't keep my hands off you.
That's the truth.

58:42.925 --> 58:45.553
That's what's so wonderful
about you in that...

58:45.678 --> 58:47.305
bestial sort of way.

58:52.018 --> 58:53.102
Woman.

58:59.942 --> 59:01.777
This better be earth-shattering.

59:08.784 --> 59:10.161
This is to Raoul.

59:12.538 --> 59:14.174
Yeah, Vincent Hanna.

59:56.508 --> 59:58.301
Here's how we found her.

01:00:02.430 --> 01:00:03.473
How old?

01:00:03.598 --> 01:00:06.643
Sixteen, seventeen.
Been here about six hours.

01:00:07.477 --> 01:00:08.895
How'd she die?

01:00:09.020 --> 01:00:12.399
Beat her head in, same as the others.
Cerebral hematoma.

01:00:15.318 --> 01:00:16.444
Who's that?

01:00:17.028 --> 01:00:18.280
Mother and siblings.

01:00:18.405 --> 01:00:20.198
- Why are they here?
- It's fucked up.

01:00:20.323 --> 01:00:23.201
Somebody inside knew the girl
and called the family.

01:00:24.369 --> 01:00:25.495
Let's go.

01:00:30.292 --> 01:00:31.334
Nice.

01:00:32.294 --> 01:00:36.256
My intuition says the DNA check on
the semen will show it's the same guy...

01:00:36.381 --> 01:00:39.426
so it's a series and ending up
in your court.

01:00:39.801 --> 01:00:41.344
Sheriff's getting anywhere?

01:00:41.469 --> 01:00:42.679
Not yet.

01:00:44.055 --> 01:00:45.515
Get off of me!

01:00:48.476 --> 01:00:49.686
Oh, my God!

01:00:54.074 --> 01:00:55.242
Where is she?

01:00:55.576 --> 01:00:57.119
Easy, easy, easy.

01:01:00.414 --> 01:01:01.874
Please, come on.

01:01:04.793 --> 01:01:06.629
It's okay.

01:01:07.922 --> 01:01:09.381
Where is my baby?

01:01:09.590 --> 01:01:10.716
Where is she?

01:01:11.592 --> 01:01:13.761
I need to know what happened.

01:01:56.011 --> 01:01:58.097
I guess the earth shattered.

01:01:58.931 --> 01:02:01.684
So why didn't you let Bosko
take you home?

01:02:03.644 --> 01:02:05.896
I didn't want to ruin their night, too.

01:02:06.355 --> 01:02:07.648
What was it?

01:02:09.775 --> 01:02:11.235
You don't want to know.

01:02:11.360 --> 01:02:14.196
I'd like to know what's behind
that grim look on your face.

01:02:14.321 --> 01:02:16.740
I don't do that. You know it. Let's go.

01:02:17.408 --> 01:02:20.077
