This regular-type life like your life?

01:30:06.515 --> 01:30:08.475
My life? No, my life...

01:30:10.268 --> 01:30:11.937
My life's a disaster zone.

01:30:13.814 --> 01:30:16.316
I got a stepdaughter so fucked up...

01:30:16.900 --> 01:30:19.945
because her real father
is this large-type asshole.

01:30:20.070 --> 01:30:21.113
I got a wife.

01:30:21.238 --> 01:30:24.074
We're passing each other
on the down slope of a marriage.

01:30:24.199 --> 01:30:25.242
My third.

01:30:27.452 --> 01:30:31.164
Because I spend all my time
chasing guys like you around the block.

01:30:31.290 --> 01:30:32.582
That's my life.

01:30:39.089 --> 01:30:40.841
A guy told me one time:

01:30:42.676 --> 01:30:47.055
"Don't get attached to anything
you can't walk out on in 30 seconds...

01:30:47.180 --> 01:30:49.601
"if you feel the heat around the corner."

01:30:51.110 --> 01:30:54.280
If you're on me and you got to move
when I move...

01:30:54.697 --> 01:30:57.700
how do you expect to keep a marriage?

01:30:59.577 --> 01:31:01.370
That's an interesting point.

01:31:02.955 --> 01:31:04.206
Are you a monk?

01:31:05.541 --> 01:31:06.751
I have a woman.

01:31:07.335 --> 01:31:08.794
What do you tell her?

01:31:11.255 --> 01:31:12.923
I tell her I'm a salesman.

01:31:19.764 --> 01:31:22.767
So, if you spot me coming
around that corner...

01:31:23.809 --> 01:31:25.686
you'll just walk out on her?

01:31:27.271 --> 01:31:28.856
Not say good-bye?

01:31:29.649 --> 01:31:31.275
That's the discipline.

01:31:32.151 --> 01:31:33.944
That's pretty vacant.

01:31:34.153 --> 01:31:35.780
It is what it is.

01:31:35.905 --> 01:31:38.658
It's that, or we both better go
do something else.

01:31:40.707 --> 01:31:42.668
I don't know how to do anything else.

01:31:43.168 --> 01:31:44.586
Neither do I.

01:31:47.422 --> 01:31:48.966
I don't want to either.

01:31:49.758 --> 01:31:50.926
Neither do I.

01:31:58.642 --> 01:32:01.228
You know, I have this recurring dream.

01:32:03.146 --> 01:32:06.066
I'm sitting at this big banquet table and...

01:32:06.191 --> 01:32:09.736
all the victims of all the murders
I ever worked are there...

01:32:09.861 --> 01:32:13.782
and they're staring at me
with these black eyeballs...

01:32:14.449 --> 01:32:18.370
because they got eight-ball hemorrhages
from the head wounds.

01:32:19.663 --> 01:32:22.791
And there they are,
these big balloon people...

01:32:23.208 --> 01:32:26.586
because I found them two weeks
after they'd been under the bed.

01:32:27.379 --> 01:32:29.846
The neighbors reported the smell...

01:32:30.850 --> 01:32:32.435
and there they are...

01:32:32.560 --> 01:32:34.270
all just sitting there.

01:32:36.522 --> 01:32:37.690
What do they say?

01:32:39.734 --> 01:32:40.735
Nothing.

01:32:41.193 --> 01:32:42.361
No talk?

01:32:44.572 --> 01:32:46.324
They have nothing to say.

01:32:47.241 --> 01:32:49.201
We just look at each other.

01:32:50.202 --> 01:32:51.829
They look at me...

01:32:52.371 --> 01:32:54.498
and that's it. That's the dream.

01:32:57.376 --> 01:32:59.211
I have one where I'm drowning.

01:33:00.004 --> 01:33:03.633
I gotta wake myself up and start breathing
or I'll die in my sleep.

01:33:05.760 --> 01:33:07.094
Know what that's about?

01:33:08.763 --> 01:33:10.181
Having enough time.

01:33:11.891 --> 01:33:13.059
Enough time...

01:33:13.517 --> 01:33:15.227
to do what you want to do?

01:33:15.436 --> 01:33:16.687
That's right.

01:33:19.231 --> 01:33:20.566
You doing it now?

01:33:20.775 --> 01:33:21.984
No, not yet.

01:33:27.615 --> 01:33:29.575
You know, we're sitting here...

01:33:30.951 --> 01:33:33.162
like a couple of regular fellas.

01:33:33.287 --> 01:33:36.123
You do what you do,
and I do what I gotta do.

01:33:38.250 --> 01:33:40.586
Now that we've been face to face...

01:33:43.589 --> 01:33:46.217
if I'm there and I gotta put you away...

01:33:46.592 --> 01:33:48.052
I won't like it.

01:33:48.928 --> 01:33:50.054
But, I tell you...

01:33:52.640 --> 01:33:54.600
if it's between you...

01:33:54.809 --> 01:33:58.604
and some poor bastard whose wife
you're gonna turn into a widow...

01:33:59.605 --> 01:34:00.773
brother...

01:34:01.273 --> 01:34:03.109
you are going down.

01:34:15.672 --> 01:34:17.966
There's a flip side to that coin.

01:34:20.301 --> 01:34:22.470
What if you do got me boxed in...

01:34:22.929 --> 01:34:24.681
and I gotta put you down?

01:34:25.849 --> 01:34:27.559
Because no matter what...

01:34:28.059 --> 01:34:30.020
you won't get in my way.

01:34:31.354 --> 01:34:33.565
We've been face to face, yeah.

01:34:36.860 --> 01:34:38.570
But I will not hesitate.

01:34:38.903 --> 01:34:40.238
Not for a second.

01:34:46.786 --> 01:34:48.246
Maybe that'll happen.

01:34:50.999 --> 01:34:52.000
Or...

01:34:52.375 --> 01:34:53.668
who knows?

01:34:54.294 --> 01:34:56.629
Maybe we'll never see each other again.

01:35:12.538 --> 01:35:14.039
They dumped us.

01:35:15.332 --> 01:35:16.375
What?

01:35:16.833 --> 01:35:18.293
They dumped us.

01:35:18.919 --> 01:35:20.128
What do you mean?

01:35:20.254 --> 01:35:21.505
Chris slipped away.

01:35:21.630 --> 01:35:23.507
He doesn't talk about their scores...

01:35:23.632 --> 01:35:26.968
so there's nothing for me to get
from Marciano. I just tried.

01:35:27.343 --> 01:35:29.303
- What about Cheritto?
- Same.

01:35:29.428 --> 01:35:32.056
Transponders got put on a bus
to San Clemente.

01:35:34.767 --> 01:35:36.519
They dumped all our surveillance?

01:35:36.644 --> 01:35:38.854
Yes, at the same time. 9:00 p.m.

01:35:40.147 --> 01:35:43.359
I had coffee with McCauley
half an hour ago!

01:35:43.484 --> 01:35:44.527
We were on you.

01:35:44.652 --> 01:35:48.531
Then McCauley drives in to LAX
where surveillance can't fly over.

01:35:49.282 --> 01:35:51.668
His car's still there. He's gone.

01:35:57.132 --> 01:36:01.636
Does anybody have any idea
where the fuck these people are?

01:37:01.487 --> 01:37:02.529
Hear from him?

01:37:03.447 --> 01:37:07.409
Not a thing. And not hearing
bothers me more. Where's this guy?

01:37:09.954 --> 01:37:10.955
This guy...

01:37:11.080 --> 01:37:12.540
we put him on.

01:37:12.665 --> 01:37:14.291
Says he knows McCauley.

01:37:20.047 --> 01:37:21.048
Who are you?

01:37:22.258 --> 01:37:23.425
Waingro.

01:37:24.009 --> 01:37:25.636
My name's Waingro.

01:37:26.011 --> 01:37:29.181
I've been living in this office.
How well do you know him?

01:37:30.608 --> 01:37:33.068
We took some major scores together.

01:37:37.030 --> 01:37:38.907
Why haven't I heard from him?

01:37:39.032 --> 01:37:40.909
He's probably busy right now.

01:37:41.535 --> 01:37:43.161
But he's real thorough.

01:37:44.538 --> 01:37:46.665
He ain't going to forget about you.

01:37:46.999 --> 01:37:48.375
That's reassuring.

01:37:50.210 --> 01:37:52.671
I got some moves I could make here.

01:37:53.797 --> 01:37:56.008
Probably be a big help to you.

01:38:17.570 --> 01:38:19.196
You recognize the grill man?

01:38:26.662 --> 01:38:27.705
No.

01:38:27.830 --> 01:38:28.873
Folsom.

01:38:28.998 --> 01:38:31.334
D-block. Housed with Dobie Rush.

01:38:33.002 --> 01:38:34.462
I ain't got my break yet.

01:38:34.587 --> 01:38:36.756
Cisco and Pancho didn't show.

01:38:37.006 --> 01:38:39.633
Haul out the garbage. Mop up the back.

01:38:39.966 --> 01:38:41.676
Take your break later.

01:38:42.052 --> 01:38:43.470
Piece of shit.

01:38:43.887 --> 01:38:45.013
Pick up!

01:38:48.350 --> 01:38:49.768
Where the hell is he?

01:38:49.893 --> 01:38:52.103
I want to check the slot for the work car.

01:38:52.312 --> 01:38:53.396
So did I.

01:39:01.363 --> 01:39:02.405
Hang on.

01:39:05.408 --> 01:39:10.172
Use the land line. Call me at 103-7206.

01:39:21.976 --> 01:39:23.143
Where are you?

01:39:23.269 --> 01:39:25.980
There's cops all over me, man,
like a cheap suit.

01:39:26.981 --> 01:39:28.315
I can't dump them.

01:39:31.068 --> 01:39:32.861
They know you see them?

01:39:33.153 --> 01:39:35.030
They're doing parallels.

01:39:37.741 --> 01:39:39.285
I can try to dump them again.

01:39:39.410 --> 01:39:41.370
<i>How are we going to know if you did?</i>

01:39:41.495 --> 01:39:43.121
If not, you'll draw them to us.

01:39:43.705 --> 01:39:44.789
Go to Ventura.

01:39:44.914 --> 01:39:46.165
<i>Pull them out of here.</i>

01:39:46.291 --> 01:39:49.752
I'm sorry. Last thing I wanted to do
was let you down.

01:40:16.362 --> 01:40:17.405
Pick up.

01:40:19.908 --> 01:40:21.409
Neil, man. What's up?

01:40:21.618 --> 01:40:22.660
What's up?

01:40:22.785 --> 01:40:24.495
What are you doing here?

01:40:24.787 --> 01:40:28.249
I'm looking for a driver
who can handle scanners on the radio.

01:40:28.374 --> 01:40:29.667
Right now, today.

01:40:30.043 --> 01:40:31.336
You remember the drill?

01:40:31.461 --> 01:40:32.712
Yeah, sure.

01:40:32.921 --> 01:40:34.047
You cool?

01:40:34.797 --> 01:40:36.424
You know I'm cool.

01:40:37.217 --> 01:40:39.594
One answer: Yes or no. Right now.

01:40:53.824 --> 01:40:56.619
Yeah, man. Fuck, yeah. You're on.

01:40:57.995 --> 01:40:59.538
Out back in five.

01:41:10.007 --> 01:41:11.384
What's burning?

01:41:11.926 --> 01:41:13.135
What is this?

01:41:13.636 --> 01:41:15.638
Where do you think you're going?

01:42:51.950 --> 01:42:53.993
Don't move! Put your hands in the air!

01:42:54.160 --> 01:42:55.202
Hands up!

01:42:55.369 --> 01:42:56.995
Put them up! Now!

01:42:58.372 --> 01:42:59.456
Get on your knees!

01:42:59.623 --> 01:43:00.624
The keys!

01:43:01.625 --> 01:43:03.085
Get on your knees!

01:43:07.464 --> 01:43:08.590
Get over there!

01:43:10.008 --> 01:43:11.093
Turn around!

01:43:11.301 --> 01:43:12.844
Put your hands behind you!

01:43:12.970 --> 01:43:14.012
Get down!

01:43:14.137 --> 01:43:15.180
Stay down!

01:43:16.223 --> 01:43:17.224
Get down!

01:43:20.018 --> 01:43:22.437
- Down!
- The keys! The keys!

01:43:27.317 --> 01:43:28.360
Stay down!

01:43:29.152 --> 01:43:32.155
We want to hurt no one.
We want the bank's money, not yours.

01:43:32.281 --> 01:43:35.284
Your money is insured by the government.
You won't lose a dime.

01:43:35.409 --> 01:43:36.577
Think of your families.

01:43:36.702 --> 01:43:39.162
Don't risk your life. Don't be a hero.

01:43:39.538 --> 01:43:44.251
I want you to sit on the floor, put your
hands on your head. Anybody feels sick...

01:43:44.376 --> 01:43:46.920
anybody got heart trouble,
lean against the wall.

01:43:48.338 --> 01:43:49.339
The key.

01:43:49.548 --> 01:43:50.799
What key?

01:43:52.759 --> 01:43:54.803
Sit down and stay down!

01:43:55.846 --> 01:43:58.473
Sit there. Don't move. Let it bleed.

01:44:47.781 --> 01:44:49.741
Get down. Down, down, down.

01:44:49.991 --> 01:44:51.451
Put your heads down!

01:45:17.017 --> 01:45:19.353
You guys working a case
on a Neil McCauley?

01:45:19.478 --> 01:45:22.690
This C.I., Hugh Benny,
called in about a bank.

01:45:25.859 --> 01:45:28.821
Far East National Bank, 11:30!

01:45:46.297 --> 01:45:48.591
I want a block at Figueroa and Fifth...

01:45:48.716 --> 01:45:51.769
and I want a block
northbound Flower at Sixth.

01:46:30.014 --> 01:46:31.766
They're already coming out.

01:46:32.350 --> 01:46:34.393
We gotta take them in the car.

01:46:34.560 --> 01:46:36.354
Wait till they are all in.

01:46:36.604 --> 01:46:38.898
Get clean shots. Watch your background.

01:46:48.449 --> 01:46:49.825
Police! Move!

01:46:51.285 --> 01:46:52.662
Move. Move. Get down.

01:47:14.808 --> 01:47:16.142
Move it. Down, down.

01:47:19.646 --> 01:47:20.814
We did it!

01:47:25.318 --> 01:47:26.361
Move!

01:47:32.668 --> 01:47:33.877
Get down!

01:47:43.429 --> 01:47:44.471
Get in the car!

01:48:01.238 --> 01:48:02.448
Go! Go!

01:49:03.347 --> 01:49:04.390
Go!

01:49:29.298 --> 01:49:30.299
Go!

01:51:11.407 --> 01:51:12.408
Come on!

01:51:45.440 --> 01:51:46.733
Get down!

01:51:59.871 --> 01:52:03.791
All the way down! Get down! Now!

01:53:03.943 --> 01:53:05.236
Come here.

01:53:50.780 --> 01:53:52.073
I got you.

01:53:56.411 --> 01:54:00.790
<i>Tragedy in the neighborhood today.
A bank robbery spilled out into the street.</i>

01:54:01.166 --> 01:54:04.169
<i>Claudia Newman, live on the scene.
She has the latest.</i>

01:54:04.419 --> 01:54:08.381
<i>This afternoon, a neighborhood was
terrorized by a bank holdup gone wrong.</i>

01:54:08.590 --> 01:54:12.311
<i>With the streets full of shoppers and kids,
police and armed robbers...</i>

01:54:12.436 --> 01:54:13.854
Excuse me, bartender.

01:54:14.063 --> 01:54:17.900
<i>Our top story tonight:
Robbery, pursuit and, finally, death.</i>

01:54:18.025 --> 01:54:21.152
<i>A Los Angeles neighborhood is shaken
by a bank robbery...</i>

01:54:21.361 --> 01:54:23.780
<i>that ended in homicide and terror.</i>

01:54:24.072 --> 01:54:25.490
<i>Michael Cheritto...</i>

01:54:25.615 --> 01:54:29.661
<i>one of four men involved
in the foiled robbery, died at the scene.</i>

01:54:29.786 --> 01:54:31.037
<i>Also fatally wounded:</i>

01:54:31.162 --> 01:54:34.457
<i>Another suspect, Donald Breedan,
who died of gunshot wounds...</i>

01:54:34.582 --> 01:54:38.169
<i>during the extensive gunfire
between police and suspects.</i>

01:54:40.296 --> 01:54:41.756
All right, hold him.

01:54:42.090 --> 01:54:43.590
It's all right.

01:54:51.640 --> 01:54:52.683
So?

01:54:52.808 --> 01:54:54.810
He's got blood loss and shock.

01:54:54.935 --> 01:54:58.689
I'll give you quarter-grain bottles
of morphine for the pain.

01:54:59.564 --> 01:55:00.691
Bottom line?

01:55:01.233 --> 01:55:03.944
It's mostly tissue damage, which is good.

01:55:04.403 --> 01:55:06.780
His clavicle's fractured. Can you rest?

01:55:07.489 --> 01:55:08.573
Six, seven hours.

01:55:08.699 --> 01:55:10.242
- That's it?
- That's it.

01:55:10.659 --> 01:55:12.119
Take off your shirt.

01:55:12.244 --> 01:55:13.245
What?

01:55:14.746 --> 01:55:16.206
Take off your shirt.

01:55:24.715 --> 01:55:26.091
My daughter gave it to me.

01:55:26.216 --> 01:55:28.385
I don't give a shit. Take it off.

01:55:40.772 --> 01:55:41.940
Listen to me.

01:55:42.357 --> 01:55:46.320
Nate's going to pick you up.
He's going to take you to his place.

01:55:47.695 --> 01:55:48.779
Where's Charlene?

01:55:48.904 --> 01:55:53.293
We gotta go. We're on the 6:00 news.
We gotta get out of here.

01:55:53.418 --> 01:55:55.420
I'm not going without her.

01:55:55.795 --> 01:55:57.088
Think about that.

01:55:57.422 --> 01:55:59.215
I will meet you at Nate's.

01:55:59.466 --> 01:56:00.759
Where are you going?

01:56:00.925 --> 01:56:04.679
To find out if our out got spilled
along with every other damn thing.

01:56:05.180 --> 01:56:06.431
Who did it?

01:56:07.807 --> 01:56:09.100
Who wasn't there?

01:56:10.602 --> 01:56:11.603
Trejo.

01:56:15.482 --> 01:56:17.025
See you at Nate's.

01:56:25.367 --> 01:56:26.743
You still want me?

01:56:27.160 --> 01:56:30.288
You come down here right now
and get me. Dominick and me.

01:56:31.539 --> 01:56:32.666
<i>Okay, baby.</i>

01:56:33.124 --> 01:56:35.085
<i>I'll be there in two hours.</i>

01:56:36.419 --> 01:56:37.462
All right.

01:56:39.506 --> 01:56:41.299
Goddamn you, Chris.

01:56:41.424 --> 01:56:42.550
Goddamn you.

01:56:43.551 --> 01:56:45.762
You're on a plane to Los Angeles.

01:56:46.012 --> 01:56:47.055
Right.

01:57:35.403 --> 01:57:37.530
Why did you do it? What happened?

01:57:38.906 --> 01:57:40.450
- They made me.
- Who?

01:57:40.616 --> 01:57:41.826
Where's Anna?

01:57:43.244 --> 01:57:44.370
She's dead.

01:57:47.332 --> 01:57:50.418
So is Michael and Breedan,
the guy who stood in for you.

01:57:50.960 --> 01:57:52.086
Who did it?

01:57:52.253 --> 01:57:53.254
Who did it?

01:57:53.379 --> 01:57:55.089
They had Anna, man.

01:57:55.256 --> 01:57:56.257
Who?

01:57:57.674 --> 01:57:58.800
Waingro.

01:57:59.593 --> 01:58:00.802
Waingro.

01:58:01.595 --> 01:58:02.721
On his own?

01:58:04.765 --> 01:58:06.475
- For someone.
- Who?

01:58:07.768 --> 01:58:10.062
The other he worked for.

01:58:11.271 --> 01:58:12.481
Van Zant.

01:58:15.484 --> 01:58:16.777
Van Zant?

01:58:21.072 --> 01:58:22.239
Are you sure?

01:58:22.823 --> 01:58:24.075
Van Zant.

01:58:25.868 --> 01:58:28.204
Did you tell them how we're getting out?

01:58:29.330 --> 01:58:30.790
I don't think so.

01:58:31.499 --> 01:58:32.667
Come on.

01:58:34.543 --> 01:58:36.087
I don't remember.

01:58:41.509 --> 01:58:42.635
I'll call a medic.

01:58:42.760 --> 01:58:44.595
I'm not going to make it.

01:58:46.889 --> 01:58:48.975
I can't feel nothing.

01:58:51.227 --> 01:58:53.104
My Anna's gone.

01:58:55.314 --> 01:58:56.941
She's gone.

01:58:58.985 --> 01:59:00.944
Don't leave me like this.

01:59:01.987 --> 01:59:03.488
Please, homes.

01:59:04.614 --> 01:59:06.574
Don't leave me like this.

01:59:33.527 --> 01:59:35.988
You on a cellular? Use a hard line.

01:59:36.905 --> 01:59:38.157
It's a new one.

01:59:39.616 --> 01:59:42.077
The guy lives on Hillside Terrace, Encino.

01:59:42.453 --> 01:59:43.829
10725.

01:59:44.204 --> 01:59:45.581
<i>10725.</i>

01:59:45.914 --> 01:59:46.999
<i>Chris?</i>

01:59:47.499 --> 01:59:49.209
He's with me, my place.

01:59:49.543 --> 01:59:51.879
Next, Waingro, okay?

01:59:53.714 --> 01:59:55.007
You got the time?

01:59:56.008 --> 01:59:57.384
I'll make time.

01:59:57.760 --> 01:59:59.511
And I need a new out.

02:00:00.220 --> 02:00:01.347
Is it blown?

02:00:03.140 --> 02:00:04.767
How can I trust it?

02:00:07.894 --> 02:00:09.020
You got it.

02:00:10.063 --> 02:00:11.522
Stay healthy.

02:00:17.070 --> 02:00:18.696
Charlene Shiherlis.

02:00:19.614 --> 02:00:22.533
Drucker's got a safe house in Venice
to stash her in.

02:00:22.659 --> 02:00:24.160
Neil's transportation.

02:00:24.285 --> 02:00:28.122
Get on the phone. Somewhere, someone's
trying to put it together for him.

02:00:28.581 --> 02:00:30.958
You don't believe he already had a plan?

02:00:31.084 --> 02:00:32.669
Sure. Now he needs another.

02:00:32.794 --> 02:00:34.921
Would you trust yours
after this afternoon?

02:00:36.589 --> 02:00:39.050
This rat motherfucker,
where did we get him?

02:00:39.175 --> 02:00:42.720
He's a C.I. For a burglary cop.
Called in the tip on the bank.

02:00:42.929 --> 02:00:44.514
On Neil McCauley.

02:00:44.722 --> 02:00:46.182
How much time we got?

02:00:46.641 --> 02:00:51.279
Eight, ten hours for him to set up
a new out. After that, he's gone, bye-bye.

02:01:44.999 --> 02:01:47.752
You ratted McCauley to us!
How'd you know?

02:01:48.002 --> 02:01:49.295
Who told you?

02:01:49.670 --> 02:01:51.964
Who told you, rat motherfucker?

02:01:52.340 --> 02:01:53.382
Who?

02:02:38.059 --> 02:02:39.519
Waingro, where is he?

02:02:40.561 --> 02:02:41.688
Where?

02:02:41.813 --> 02:02:43.106
How would I know?

02:03:08.881 --> 02:03:09.882
Well...

02:03:10.466 --> 02:03:12.218
what do we have here?

02:03:13.177 --> 02:03:14.345
This pretty?

02:03:14.470 --> 02:03:15.555
This pretty?

02:03:19.182 --> 02:03:20.642
You piece of shit.

02:03:20.767 --> 02:03:23.770
Told me you wanted out from under.
You're scared, right?

02:03:23.895 --> 02:03:25.647
You want out? This is out.

02:03:25.772 --> 02:03:28.984
- Yeah, what's your end?
- I don't need no stupid broad.

02:03:29.568 --> 02:03:30.944
How'd I get into this?

02:03:31.069 --> 02:03:32.112
Easy.

02:03:32.904 --> 02:03:35.240
You heard me. She had a rough ride.

02:03:35.615 --> 02:03:36.742
Fix her a drink.

02:03:36.867 --> 02:03:38.702
Look in the cabinet above the sink.

02:03:38.827 --> 02:03:39.870
Fuck her.

02:03:42.289 --> 02:03:44.916
You better get in there and stay in there.

02:03:48.503 --> 02:03:49.880
Lookie here.

02:03:51.423 --> 02:03:54.134
My name is Sgt. Drucker, LAPD Homicide.

02:03:54.259 --> 02:03:56.053
You want to put Dominick
in the bedroom?

02:03:56.178 --> 02:03:57.929
He stays with me.

02:04:08.065 --> 02:04:09.442
So, what now?

02:04:12.286 --> 02:04:13.371
He's right.

02:04:13.496 --> 02:04:15.498
You want out? This is out.

02:04:17.375 --> 02:04:19.585
You believe you have to betray Chris?

02:04:19.710 --> 02:04:20.920
No shit.

02:04:21.504 --> 02:04:23.880
That's right. You would have to.

02:04:24.506 --> 02:04:28.343
See, if you don't betray Chris,
you victimize Dominick.

02:04:29.344 --> 02:04:32.806
'Cause he'll be an orphan
when you go to prison as an accessory...

02:04:32.931 --> 02:04:37.644
'cause you got no parents to take him.
So he ends up raised in foster homes...

02:04:37.769 --> 02:04:39.646
juvenile facilities.

02:04:39.896 --> 02:04:41.648
Then he steals a car.

02:04:42.357 --> 02:04:47.237
Then he winds up in gladiator academies
like Chino and Tracy.

02:04:47.862 --> 02:04:50.115
Fucked for life.

02:04:51.324 --> 02:04:53.994
You know what happens,
because you've been there.

02:04:55.662 --> 02:04:59.960
Dominick didn't get a chance yet
to choose his life. But Chris did.

02:05:01.966 --> 02:05:04.677
If you give up Chris, you get off clean.

02:05:05.678 --> 02:05:07.013
You can do it...

02:05:07.388 --> 02:05:09.640
for your kid, so you can raise him.

02:05:13.686 --> 02:05:15.021
What else are you selling?

02:05:15.146 --> 02:05:16.522
All kinds of shit.

02:05:18.024 --> 02:05:22.820
But I don't have to sell this, you know it.
This kind of shit here sells itself.

02:05:29.576 --> 02:05:31.119
<i>Here's an update.</i>

02:05:31.244 --> 02:05:32.787
Drucker's on Line 2.

02:05:32.912 --> 02:05:34.414
<i>Hold on for a second.</i>

02:05:37.292 --> 02:05:39.210
Drucker's on the other line.

02:05:39.878 --> 02:05:41.087
Conference him in.

02:05:42.339 --> 02:05:43.381
Go ahead.

02:05:43.757 --> 02:05:45.383
Vincent, it's me.

02:05:48.094 --> 02:05:50.230
One answer. What's it going to be?

02:05:57.237 --> 02:05:59.740
We're set here. She'll make the call.

02:05:59.865 --> 02:06:02.951
That's good. Here's the deal.

02:06:03.369 --> 02:06:06.497
Hugh Benny has reformed
his wayward life...

02:06:06.622 --> 02:06:09.083
and become a born-again good citizen.

02:06:09.416 --> 02:06:13.629
Apparently, Neil got sold out to us
by this cowboy named Waingro.

02:06:14.046 --> 02:06:18.842
Waingro used to be a part of Neil's crew,
then went to work for a money launderer:

02:06:18.967 --> 02:06:20.219
<i>Van Zant.</i>

02:06:20.928 --> 02:06:23.930
Units are at Van Zant's house
as we speak...

02:06:24.055 --> 02:06:26.182
because he got shot dead earlier tonight.

02:06:26.766 --> 02:06:30.019
<i>If Neil goes after anybody else,
it's going to be Waingro.</i>

02:06:30.269 --> 02:06:33.772
Waingro just got himself a suite
at the Airport Marquis...

02:06:33.897 --> 02:06:35.774
under the name Jamieson.

02:06:36.024 --> 02:06:40.570
He's there now. I want you to get that
to bail bondsmen, bookies...

02:06:40.696 --> 02:06:43.657
<i>assignment officers
and snitches in County.</i>

02:06:43.782 --> 02:06:48.120
Anyone you can think of who'll put it
on the street. Deploy a team at the hotel...

02:06:48.245 --> 02:06:50.706
<i>and personally check their coms
every 30 minutes.</i>

02:06:50.831 --> 02:06:53.208
Because maybe Neil will go for him.

02:06:53.500 --> 02:06:54.793
How're you feeling?

02:06:55.585 --> 02:06:57.129
Banged up, but I'll live.

02:07:06.346 --> 02:07:07.681
He's here.

02:07:08.432 --> 02:07:10.058
Neil is still here.

02:07:11.268 --> 02:07:12.728
I can feel it.

02:07:13.603 --> 02:07:15.022
For how long?

02:07:16.565 --> 02:07:18.483
Seven, eight hours, max.

02:07:27.909 --> 02:07:29.202
What did you do?

02:07:29.792 --> 02:07:30.838
That was you?

02:07:31.213 --> 02:07:33.090
I don't sell metal.

02:07:33.799 --> 02:07:36.843
Would have been okay, you fly out after.
Now it's jammed.

02:07:36.968 --> 02:07:38.511
We gotta go together.

02:07:39.012 --> 02:07:41.348
Those other people were with you?

02:07:42.891 --> 02:07:44.476
My friend, Michael...

02:07:46.227 --> 02:07:48.146
he knew the risks.

02:07:52.692 --> 02:07:54.694
When it rains, you get wet.

02:07:57.530 --> 02:07:59.074
Get packed. Let's go.

02:08:18.551 --> 02:08:20.470
Why did you do this to me?

02:08:32.065 --> 02:08:33.400
It'll be all right.

02:08:33.525 --> 02:08:35.443
Do you understand?

02:08:40.115 --> 02:08:41.865
It's going to be all right.

02:08:53.335 --> 02:08:56.463
There's a Camaro at this address,
Level D, Slot 18.

02:09:01.760 --> 02:09:03.220
Here's some cash.

02:09:06.223 --> 02:09:07.474
When is it over?

02:09:10.945 --> 02:09:12.613
Twenty-two hours from now.

02:09:12.989 --> 02:09:16.951
- Then we get out of here clean.
- When will you let me leave?

02:09:20.580 --> 02:09:21.581
Go now.

02:09:21.706 --> 02:09:23.666
You want out? There's the door.

02:09:24.292 --> 02:09:26.252
Will you let me leave later?

02:09:31.424 --> 02:09:32.967
It will be different.

02:09:34.635 --> 02:09:36.346
Do you even understand?

02:10:07.334 --> 02:10:08.668
It's ready.

02:10:16.385 --> 02:10:18.178
This is my friend Ralph.

02:10:18.845 --> 02:10:20.806
You didn't tell me you were...

02:10:21.682 --> 02:10:23.016
Oh, my God!

02:10:23.225 --> 02:10:24.434
Where's Lauren?

02:10:24.810 --> 02:10:26.560
She's at Lisa-Beth's.

02:10:27.061 --> 02:10:29.188
This has nothing to do with me. I'm sorry.

02:10:29.313 --> 02:10:30.398
What for?

02:10:30.523 --> 02:10:31.649
Sit down.

02:10:32.650 --> 02:10:34.026
Don't you get angry?

02:10:34.902 --> 02:10:35.986
I'm angry.

02:10:37.738 --> 02:10:39.573
I'm very angry, Ralph.

02:10:40.324 --> 02:10:43.244
You can ball my wife if she wants you to.

02:10:44.829 --> 02:10:48.207
You can lounge around here on her sofa.

02:10:49.332 --> 02:10:51.176
In her ex-husband's...

02:10:51.719 --> 02:10:54.930
dead-tech, post-modernistic,
bullshit house...

02:10:55.055 --> 02:10:56.432
if you want to.

02:10:59.143 --> 02:11:01.353
But you do not get to watch...

02:11:01.687 --> 02:11:03.522
my fucking...

02:11:03.647 --> 02:11:04.815
television set!

02:11:04.940 --> 02:11:06.275
For God's sake.

02:11:13.157 --> 02:11:14.950
Put the television set down.

02:11:15.117 --> 02:11:17.661
- I never cheated on you, bitch.
- Maybe you should have.

02:11:17.786 --> 02:11:19.872
- I should have?
- You're a party to this.

02:11:20.039 --> 02:11:23.208
I made Ralph fuck you
because it makes me feel good.

02:11:23.333 --> 02:11:24.960
Our situation is absurd.

02:11:27.588 --> 02:11:30.382
Shut up, Ralph! Sit down!

02:11:33.302 --> 02:11:37.139
Why is it that I have to figure things out
and explain them to you?

02:11:37.347 --> 02:11:39.933
I say what I mean, and I do what I say.

02:11:40.059 --> 02:11:41.268
How admirable.

02:11:41.393 --> 02:11:43.645
- You bet.
- Except none of it's about us.

02:11:44.313 --> 02:11:45.314
No.

02:11:46.774 --> 02:11:49.735
I may be stoned on grass and Prozac but...

02:11:50.569 --> 02:11:52.654
you walk through our life dead.

02:11:53.405 --> 02:11:57.450
Now I have to demean myself with Ralph
just to get closure with you.

02:12:10.505 --> 02:12:12.882
Passports, traveler's checks, plastic.

02:12:13.424 --> 02:12:14.634
The plane...

02:12:15.093 --> 02:12:18.554
charter terminal, LAX, Hangar 17.

02:12:18.679 --> 02:12:20.306
Call letters are 1011 Sierra.

02:12:23.559 --> 02:12:24.727
Touches down...

02:12:24.852 --> 02:12:27.355
holds for you five minutes, then splits.

02:12:27.605 --> 02:12:31.159
The plane will stand an FAA check.
Filed a flight plan, the works.

02:12:33.036 --> 02:12:34.121
Where's Chris?

02:12:34.454 --> 02:12:35.497
He's gone.

02:12:36.873 --> 02:12:37.874
What?

02:12:38.542 --> 02:12:41.044
Said he's going on his own.
Went to find Charlene.

02:12:41.169 --> 02:12:43.422
- Did you bring him here?
- Yeah, I did.

02:12:44.297 --> 02:12:45.340
What happened?

02:12:46.466 --> 02:12:48.009
It's a free country.

02:12:53.265 --> 02:12:55.058
Check in with me at 9:00...

02:12:55.350 --> 02:12:57.102
everything is still cool.

02:12:58.978 --> 02:13:00.104
All right.

02:13:23.294 --> 02:13:25.755
I don't know what I'm doing anymore.

02:13:29.091 --> 02:13:30.885
I know life is short.

02:13:31.552 --> 02:13:33.596
Whatever time you get is luck.

02:13:36.348 --> 02:13:37.892
You want to walk?

02:13:40.770 --> 02:13:42.521
You walk right now...

02:13:44.148 --> 02:13:45.733
all on your own.

02:13:46.442 --> 02:13:49.070
On your own you choose to come with me.

02:13:55.493 --> 02:13:57.078
All I know is...

02:13:59.372 --> 02:14:02.999
there's no point in me
going anywhere anymore...

02:14:04.209 --> 02:14:06.169
if it's going to be alone...

02:14:07.253 --> 02:14:08.755
without you.

02:15:08.822 --> 02:15:09.906
I got a live one.

02:15:10.866 --> 02:15:12.242
I'll hold.

02:15:14.703 --> 02:15:16.163
Show yourself.

02:15:17.289 --> 02:15:19.332
- Do it.
- Shut up!

02:15:23.211 --> 02:15:25.422
Now, just one second at the window...

02:15:26.715 --> 02:15:28.467
and it's all over.

02:17:18.500 --> 02:17:19.543
Hey, man...

02:17:21.335 --> 02:17:24.590
you know any place to rent around here?

02:17:27.968 --> 02:17:30.103
The grocer has got cards on the wall.

02:17:42.282 --> 02:17:43.409
It's not him.

02:17:43.534 --> 02:17:44.869
It's not Chris.

02:17:53.044 --> 02:17:54.712
Unit 2, this is Command.

02:17:55.213 --> 02:17:56.589
Take him at the street.

02:17:56.714 --> 02:17:57.882
Check him out.

02:18:25.534 --> 02:18:26.951
He's John Peterson.

02:18:27.076 --> 02:18:29.036
<i>Valid ID. Car's registered to...</i>

02:18:29.161 --> 02:18:31.580
<i>Bukowski, Gene.</i>

02:18:31.914 --> 02:18:33.124
<i>Ran it to DMV.</i>

02:18:33.249 --> 02:18:34.500
<i>It's clean.</i>

02:18:37.420 --> 02:18:38.629
Let him go.

02:18:39.088 --> 02:18:40.172
Roger.

02:18:40.464 --> 02:18:42.424
Thank you. Have a good evening.

02:18:44.802 --> 02:18:45.886
It's no-go.

02:18:55.688 --> 02:18:58.482
Would you like a cup of coffee
while we wait?

02:18:58.607 --> 02:19:00.316
Yeah, that would be nice.

02:19:31.482 --> 02:19:32.816
What do you got?

02:19:32.941 --> 02:19:34.359
<i>Nothing's happening.</i>

02:19:47.623 --> 02:19:49.083
Hello, it's Vincent.

02:19:49.708 --> 02:19:50.751
<i>What do you got?</i>

02:19:50.876 --> 02:19:53.295
Nothing's going on. Waingro went for ice.

02:19:53.670 --> 02:19:54.755
<i>That's it.</i>

02:20:03.555 --> 02:20:04.848
You know what?

02:20:07.434 --> 02:20:08.852
Neil is gone.

02:20:13.982 --> 02:20:15.526
Flying like a bird.

02:20:16.443 --> 02:20:17.736
How do you know?

02:20:19.321 --> 02:20:20.531
We still got bait!

02:20:20.656 --> 02:20:22.699
- Maybe some time!
- What do we got?

02:20:22.825 --> 02:20:24.118
What do we got?

02:20:25.035 --> 02:20:26.995
<i>Bon voyage, motherfucker.</i>

02:20:28.497 --> 02:20:29.956
You were good.

02:20:31.791 --> 02:20:33.418
I'm going to the hotel.

02:20:34.710 --> 02:20:36.671
I'm going to take a shower...

02:20:37.714 --> 02:20:40.550
and I'm going to sleep for a month.

02:22:51.452 --> 02:22:52.494
Here.

02:22:59.626 --> 02:23:00.669
Come on.

02:23:09.344 --> 02:23:10.387
Shit.

02:23:19.688 --> 02:23:21.398
Motherfucking waste.

02:23:24.902 --> 02:23:27.863
Assholes shoot themselves all fucking day.

02:23:27.988 --> 02:23:29.031
Not you, baby.

02:23:29.156 --> 02:23:30.365
Not you.

02:23:35.704 --> 02:23:38.665
Where would she be? Her name is Lauren.

02:23:38.791 --> 02:23:41.585
Lauren Gustafson,
and she's supposed to be here.

02:23:48.966 --> 02:23:51.052
I need somebody to help...

02:23:57.225 --> 02:23:58.309
I got you.

02:23:59.644 --> 02:24:02.730
You'll be all right, I swear. It's okay, baby.

02:24:03.272 --> 02:24:04.774
Let's get a doctor!

02:24:04.899 --> 02:24:06.609
Let's go! A doctor here!

02:24:06.943 --> 02:24:09.320
- There's your mama.
- Let's just calm down.

02:24:09.447 --> 02:24:11.581
- Is she on any drugs?
- I'm calm. No.

02:24:14.126 --> 02:24:16.586
Get a trauma surgeon
and a vascular surgeon.

02:24:17.003 --> 02:24:20.465
I think she cut both arteries.
I could hardly feel her pulse.

02:24:20.841 --> 02:24:22.008
Her pressure's down.

02:24:22.134 --> 02:24:24.344
So is her respiration.
You have to intubate her.

02:24:24.469 --> 02:24:25.679
It's ready.

02:24:27.347 --> 02:24:29.349
When's the last time anybody saw her?

02:24:29.474 --> 02:24:30.475
I don't know.

02:24:30.600 --> 02:24:31.935
Where did you find her?

02:24:32.144 --> 02:24:33.270
The bathtub.

02:24:35.272 --> 02:24:37.524
Give her large-bore normal saline.

02:24:37.649 --> 02:24:39.067
Keep pressure on those bleeders.

02:24:39.192 --> 02:24:42.529
Give me two units, O-negative.
Let's type and cross her for six.

02:24:44.489 --> 02:24:47.950
Where is Respiratory? We need more help.
Get them down now.

02:24:48.075 --> 02:24:51.036
Let's have X-ray ready
for post-intubation chest X-ray.

02:24:57.376 --> 02:25:00.463
Your daughter's out of surgery
and she's in the recovery room.

02:25:00.588 --> 02:25:02.047
Her vital signs are stable.

02:25:02.214 --> 02:25:04.717
The surgeon will speak to you
in a few moments.

02:25:04.842 --> 02:25:05.926
She's okay?

02:25:06.051 --> 02:25:07.136
She's doing good.

02:25:07.261 --> 02:25:08.763
She'll be okay.

02:25:09.263 --> 02:25:11.140
She's going to be okay.

02:25:11.348 --> 02:25:14.226
Oh, my baby.
Why did she do this to herself?

02:25:15.686 --> 02:25:18.773
Look what she did.
Look what she did to herself.

02:25:23.194 --> 02:25:25.821
It's all right. It's going to be all right.

02:25:26.280 --> 02:25:28.365
I'm here. I ain't going anywhere.

02:25:28.491 --> 02:25:31.243
Do you understand?
I ain't going anywhere.

02:25:46.217 --> 02:25:47.301
It's me.

02:25:47.760 --> 02:25:50.522
Plane's in the air now.
You're right on time.

02:25:51.188 --> 02:25:53.065
I still can't find a driver...

02:25:53.232 --> 02:25:54.900
<i>so that's in the trust.</i>

02:25:55.317 --> 02:25:56.693
<i>One other thing...</i>

02:25:57.736 --> 02:25:59.613
<i>I gotta tell you.</i>

02:26:00.072 --> 02:26:04.159
The guy you want is in the Marquis
under Jamieson, if you still give a shit...

02:26:04.451 --> 02:26:06.203
<i>which I figured you wouldn't.</i>

02:26:06.495 --> 02:26:07.871
You figured right.

02:26:08.330 --> 02:26:09.873
So, so long, brother.

02:26:12.126 --> 02:26:13.585
You take it easy.

02:26:14.294 --> 02:26:15.587
You're home free.

02:26:17.673 --> 02:26:18.882
Take it easy.

02:26:29.935 --> 02:26:31.018
What is it?

02:26:31.352 --> 02:26:32.520
Nothing.

02:26:32.854 --> 02:26:34.063
Home free.

02:27:12.267 --> 02:27:14.144
I gotta take care of something.

02:27:14.311 --> 02:27:15.562
Is there time?

02:27:16.271 --> 02:27:17.439
There's time.

02:27:46.227 --> 02:27:48.854
I'll be right back. Just leave her running.

02:28:31.229 --> 02:28:32.230
<i>Registration.</i>

02:28:32.355 --> 02:28:33.440
This is room service.

02:28:33.565 --> 02:28:37.444
A Jamieson ordered a BLT, and they
screwed up his room number. What is it?

02:28:37.569 --> 02:28:39.362
<i>- They're always doing that.
- I know.</i>

02:28:39.487 --> 02:28:41.030
<i>1735.</i>

02:28:41.156 --> 02:28:42.365
Thank you.

02:30:26.101 --> 02:30:27.769
<i>Your attention, please.</i>

02:30:27.894 --> 02:30:30.939
<i>We are currently experiencing a fire alarm.</i>

02:30:31.523 --> 02:30:32.940
<i>Do not panic.</i>

02:30:33.065 --> 02:30:35.067
<i>Do not take the elevators.</i>

02:30:40.114 --> 02:30:41.532
I'm staying here.

02:30:41.657 --> 02:30:44.952
I'll check the stairs.
If there's smoke, I'll pull you out.

02:30:49.543 --> 02:30:51.843
What about her dad? Should I call him?

02:30:52.927 --> 02:30:55.138
He's somewhere in the Sierras.

02:30:57.223 --> 02:30:58.850
And she chose you.

02:31:01.478 --> 02:31:03.271
She picked your place.

02:31:05.482 --> 02:31:07.358
It's not right, what happened to her.

02:31:07.484 --> 02:31:08.943
No, it's not.

02:31:25.417 --> 02:31:27.127
Is there any way that...

02:31:29.505 --> 02:31:31.548
it could work out between us?

02:31:34.384 --> 02:31:36.720
I wish I could say yes, you know.

02:31:37.095 --> 02:31:38.138
But...

02:31:38.347 --> 02:31:39.890
in the end...

02:31:44.853 --> 02:31:46.563
It's like you said:

02:31:49.733 --> 02:31:51.068
All I am...

02:31:51.777 --> 02:31:53.862
is what I'm going after.

02:32:01.286 --> 02:32:03.455
I'm not what you want, Justine.

02:32:14.591 --> 02:32:16.510
Go on, if you have to.

02:32:19.303 --> 02:32:20.429
I'll stay.

02:32:20.555 --> 02:32:22.598
I'm okay. I can handle this.

02:32:25.643 --> 02:32:27.103
Just be careful.

02:32:27.895 --> 02:32:30.532
Call me here. Let me know you're okay.

02:32:31.658 --> 02:32:32.659
Okay?

02:33:33.469 --> 02:33:35.805
Security. There's a fire on three.

02:33:35.930 --> 02:33:37.556
We have to evacuate all floors.

02:33:37.681 --> 02:33:39.308
I can't leave here.

02:33:48.192 --> 02:33:51.195
Why don't we just talk
about this a bit, brother?

02:34:05.501 --> 02:34:06.794
He's here on 17.

02:34:09.802 --> 02:34:11.015
Look at me.

02:34:11.182 --> 02:34:12.225
Look at me!

02:34:15.603 --> 02:34:16.646
Look at me!

02:34:48.634 --> 02:34:50.011
LAPD! Don't move!

02:34:50.136 --> 02:34:51.929
Put your hands on your head!

02:35:27.507 --> 02:35:29.342
Switch me to TAC 5.

02:35:29.967 --> 02:35:31.176
Casals...

02:35:31.510 --> 02:35:32.552
JJ...

02:35:33.303 --> 02:35:34.596
Drucker, JJ...

02:35:34.721 --> 02:35:37.057
<i>I'm in the lobby level by the stairwell.</i>

02:35:37.182 --> 02:35:38.266
What have you got?

02:35:38.391 --> 02:35:41.186
<i>Teams are moving up the other elevators
to the 17th floor.</i>

02:35:41.311 --> 02:35:44.731
<i>Elevators are all out of commission
because of the fire alarm.</i>

02:35:45.190 --> 02:35:46.525
Fine. 10-4.

02:38:11.561 --> 02:38:13.104
Let me have that shotgun.

02:44:31.308 --> 02:44:33.435
Told you I'm never going back.

02:44:37.606 --> 02:44:38.648
Yeah.

